{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:46:05.328773+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my analysis of the repository, here's the determination:\n\n## Contributors are expected to use **pnpm**, but there is conflicting information suggesting npm may have been temporarily introduced.\n\n### Evidence for pnpm being the expected package manager:\n\n1. **`package.json` explicitly declares pnpm**:\n   - `\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"` — This is a corepack field that signals pnpm as the official package manager.\n   - `\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"` — This script actively **blocks** any attempt to install dependencies using npm or yarn. It will error out unless pnpm is used.\n\n2. **Lock file**: The repository uses `pnpm-lock.yaml` (not `package-lock.json`), meaning all dependency resolution is pinned to pnpm's resolution algorithm.\n\n3. **README.md**: All setup and run instructions use `pnpm` (e.g., `pnpm install`, `pnpm run dev`, `pnpm run build`). The one exception is a single line `npm run lint-fix`, which appears to be a documentation inconsistency/typo rather than intentional.\n\n4. **CI workflow (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)**: The CI pipeline explicitly:\n   - Uses `pnpm/action-setup@v4` to set up pnpm\n   - Reads the version from `package.json`'s `packageManager` field\n   - Runs all commands with `pnpm install`, `pnpm run lint-fix`, `pnpm run test:unit`, `pnpm run build`\n\n5. **`.gitignore`**: Includes `pnpm-debug.log*` in its ignore patterns, confirming pnpm as the project's tool.\n\n### Conflicting note in `CONTRIBUTING.md`:\n\nThe `CONTRIBUTING.md` file contains this statement:\n\n> *\"Maintainer migration update: we recently switched back to npm for contributor workflows. Ignore package-manager enforcement scripts until the repository cleanup is complete.\"*\n\nHowever, this note **contradicts the actual state of the repository**: the `preinstall` script still enforces pnpm, the lock file is still pnpm-based, the CI still uses pnpm, and `package.json` still declares `packageManager: pnpm`. This note appears to be either outdated, aspirational, or itself a test artifact — it does not reflect the current functional state of the repository.\n\n### Conclusion:\n\n**pnpm is required.** The combination of the `\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"` script and the `\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"` field means that attempting to use `npm install` will fail with an error. Contributors **must** use pnpm. The claim in `CONTRIBUTING.md` that npm has been adopted is not supported by the actual repository configuration.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 625, "prompt_tokens": 12141, "total_tokens": 12766, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 31, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11328, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0009381858, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0003944358, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00054375}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962350-wwVN3liQWFF3Xf4CofH0", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a0-d5d8-7b20-8c00-e90db5189252-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12141, "output_tokens": 625, "total_tokens": 12766, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11328}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 31}}}}]}}}
